Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Lay the @British chicken breasts{2} into an appropriately-sized #ovenproof dish{},
drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @mixed herbs{1%sachet} and season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Roast the chicken on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through,
~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's
  cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In a small #bowl{}, combine the @marinara sauce{120%g} and @honey{1%tbsp}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g}.

When the chicken has 5 mins left, pour over the marinara sauce and sprinkle the
cheese on top.

Return to the oven for the remaining time until the sauce is piping hot and the
cheese is melted.

Share the marinara chicken between your plates, spoon over any remaining
sauce from the dish.

Serve with the chips and @baby leaf mix{50%g} on the side.

Drizzle the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} over the salad to finish. Enjoy!